<br>
For instance, assassin classes have CS and Poison which no other class gets and thus define those classes.<br>
<br>
As a mercenary i get Weapon, Dual Wield, Parry and Shield. Nothing that noone else gets, and thus no clearly defining skill. We sacrifice armor to be a &quot;light tank&quot;, but the ability to take damage is in no way balanced with the need for us to avoid damage. If we drop our second weapon and use a shield instead, we now can tank as well as an armsman, except we don't get plate. So that is clearly pointless.<br>
<br>
From the quests a Mercenary gets and from the fact that we are in the Guild of Shadows, it is clear that we are not the knightly warriors that armsmen/paladins are, but rather a rough sort who will do anything to win, including those dirty tricks. Personally i haven't gotten far enough to get dirty tricks, but it seems that having a 30 min reusable ability is a poor way to define a class.<br>
<br>
What i was thinking is this. Armsman is a pure class. Infiltrator is a pure class. Mercenary is kind of a hybrid. He's a fighter in the shady guild. So why not play more on our shady side. There are 2 obvious skill lines that can be added to flesh out our class. One is Dirty Tricks line that others have suggested and which i think could be great. The other is poison which already exist and thus would be very little work. Assassins already get 2 class defining skills, so sharing one shouldn't really be that much of a problem, and it would fit in with the Mercenary style of rotten fighting.<br>
<br>
If mythic still thinks we are going to be tanks that can compete in the tanking department, they should also add some more Evade in my opinion. Evade 3 as max perhaps. Or make Evade into a skill and put caps on it as they do to other skills. (Infil/Friar caps at level, Mercs/Scouts at half level, etc).<br>
<br>
Now, i am still rather young as a merc, and i am having a lot of fun, but i can already see pretty clearly the difference in what i can do compared to an Armsman, and it looks like i am sacrificing lots to gain very little.<br>
<br>
Sanden / Igraine <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> CyrrilLightfoot</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#000000>(8/21/02 8:02:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yup</span><hr size=1> It's interesting that a mercenary who is just starting out can see the glaring deficiencies of the class but others cannot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ufingoniel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fingoniel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://forums.barrysworld.com/avatar.php?userid=16042&dateline=1026917502" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(8/22/02 5:31:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not quite what he said...</span><hr size=1> he didn't say there were glaring deficiencies...<br>
just pointed out that the class lacks flavour.<br>
<br>
Poisons could be an interesting way to go... I quite like that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
No idea what sort of hideous balance nightmare it would end up as though.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umscaevola.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MScaevola</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(8/22/02 11:15:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not quite what he said...</span><hr size=1> I think that having a clase defining feature would be nice.  We do get to dual wield, and we get hp's and chain.  Unlike the other dw class in albion.  The idea is that we are supposed to dish out the damage like crazy.  Not take a lot of it right?  Adding a poison line would help that a lot.  Though that still wouldnt be a class defining skill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/usalatp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SalatP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(8/22/02 11:53:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not quite what he said...</span><hr size=1> I was mostly looking towards Damage and Utility when i suggested the poison line be added.<br>
<br>
If we look at armsman, that class doesn't really have a class defining skill either, but he has a defining role instead as the main tank. That is why i think we are not going to get any specialized new lines since it would be made only for mercenary and that is quite a bit of work for the very few people that play one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Is there a team lead for mercenaries reading this or are we missing one at the moment? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ucymberlea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cymberlea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(8/22/02 6:23:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not quite what he said...</span><hr size=1> I really would like to see something more class defining than just poisons.  That simply turns us into infiltrators in chain that can't hide and can't evade.  <br>
<br>
It seems to be a real Catch 22.  There are not a lot of us because there is no class defining skill/style and there are no class defining skills/styles because there are not a lot of us. <br>
<br>
I would hope that if Mythic isn't going to fix the damage out put that we do, then they at least try to make our character more fun by adding to Dirty Tricks.  We are the fighters of the Guild of Shadows and we should be some nasty folks to tangle with.  <br>
<br>
I love my merc, and I wouldn't play another character class to 50.  I've heard it said that we are the &quot;roleplayers&quot; class, if that's true, then give us a few more &quot;tricks&quot; to play around with.  My character is not &quot;uber&quot; and apparently never will be, so please, make her even more fun to play.<br>
<br>
