In the Service of Knights Valorous <BR>
<I> "I will have justice!" </I></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ucymberlea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cymberlea</A> at: 8/22/02 6:28:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/unirala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(8/24/02 12:01:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Merc skills</span><hr size=1> I just finished reading Zauron's TL updates, wish I woulda seen those months ago :-)  I think that the Charge idea is really cool, and I also think that DW styles should do style damage on an offhand hit - just kinda makes sense. One other thing that I've thought of, that other mercs have agreed with, and just kinda makes sense for the RP aspect of our class ... why have protect 3? why not trade prot 2+3 for evade 2+3 (hell, even evade 2)?  We're mercs, we look after #1, seems to make sense to me anyway.  I also think that the parry rate should definitely be higher when using two weapons (also, just seems common sense).  One other thing that I've thought of, and I'm not sure how difficult it would be to implement ... but it would make shield spec viable for our class .... is to have shields hit just like any other offhand weapon, that way we're not gimped with a shield equiped, and a shield merc would just be way cool then.  Alright, there's my 2 cents, lemme know what ya think :-)<br>
<br>
PS:<br>
And for Pete's sake - make the 50 DW style COOL! We ARE putting 1274 pts into that line for cryin' out loud.<br>
<br>
Nirala - 45 Merc - Gawaine <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ufingoniel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fingoniel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://forums.barrysworld.com/avatar.php?userid=16042&dateline=1026917502" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#000000>(8/29/02 8:32:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> dw 50</span><hr size=1> apparently the dw 50 style is pretty cool...<br>
<br>
front positional, does about the same as amethyst slash but it doesn't eat up all your endurance... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/utallinar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tallinar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(8/30/02 3:54:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dw 50</span><hr size=1> mercenaries get dual wield...only other class in albion does is infil, however...mercs are the only ones who excel at dual wielding (unless you WANT a near worthless infil). That is what makes us unique...our job as tanks is different from armsman and paladin...we DISH the dmg, we dont take it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/unirala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(8/31/02 12:20:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dw 50</span><hr size=1> Well, I agree Tallinar that our role is to dish out damage.  The problem with this is, we don't dish out more damage than a polearmsman can (aside from enemies with PBT), given the fact that we give up a very large amount of defense being limited to chain (which evade 1, even with the new 360 degrees doesn't make up for), we should be dealing a fairly significant amount MORE damage than our plate wearing brethren.  The two suggestions that I've seen that seem to stand out the most in terms of setting the Merc apart are:<br>
<br>
1. Apply style bonus to offhand damage on a dual hit, at LEAST with DW styles, if not all styles.  And also, revise the DW line so that it's styles, especially chains, are usable in reality.  I've got 3 styles on my quickbar (at 45 - full spec Slash and DW) Amethyst Slash, and the Reflection - Hypnotic Darkness chain (have YET to have the chance to use this in RvR).  Someone said that the 50 DW style was nice, I can't say yet, but I hope it is.  The only reason I even have that chain on there though is for the stun, otherwise Amethyst Slash does more damage.  A lvl 29 Slash style, making all the DW styles up to 44 pretty much useless doesn't really seem right to me.  Could be that I'm missing something, if any of you other mercs have found otherwise, please let me know.<br>
<br>
Edit: Sorry, forgot to point out that I thought each successive move in a chain should do SIGNIFICANTLY more damage since it's harder to do. Okay, done now, I hope :-)<br>
<br>
2. A line of Dirty Tricks.  While I absolutely LOVE Increase Fumbles (once every half hour - when it's NOT resisted), having a whole line of tricks would be cool.  This is definitely something that no other class in Albion has.  I'm not sure exactly what effects they should have, or if they should be granted by level or spec (may have to consider going to 2.25 x lvl spec points if it was spec based).  Maybe we could start another topic based on new Dirty Tricks we'd like to see.<br>
<br>
Alright, well, I'm done pissin' and moanin' for now, hope I didn't annoy anyone too bad :-) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/unirala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nirala</A> at: 8/31/02 12:22:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ucarach.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(9/3/02 10:59:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dw 50</span><hr size=1> Well here is what I see as a 50 Merc. I am specced 45 Slash, 50 DW , 34 Parry. Our dmg output is ok but not what it should be. This biggest problem with dmg is in the DW styles. If you look at the styles you will see most are only medium dmg. The 50th DW style Dual Shadows while somewhat effective also carries a medium defense penalty. I have questioned this numerous times with Zauron and Mythic. Why as a merc after all these levels have my final style with such a large defensive penalty, did I suddenly become stupid after all the time it took to get there?<br>
However Lets look at the styles for DW/CD/LA. Notice anything &quot;wrong&quot;? I dang sure do. As  Mercs we have 2 high damage styles, and only available from a back position (the Shadows Edge/Penumbra combo). BMs and Zerkers have 5 High damage output styles within CD/LA. The BM 50th style in CD actually is Very High Dmg output, granted its 3rd in a chain but also carries a +defensive bonus. Side styles are not that hard to execute in RvR, Rear positional styles are way more difficult in that you are using them usually when trying to chase down an opponent and we all know what thats like, &quot;so and so is to far away to attack&quot;.<br>
<br>
Here also I think is where BMs and Mercs fall way behind in dmg to a Zerker look at the basline weapon just slash for now.<br>
Zerkers have 11 High dmg output styles in axe. What do Mercs/BMs have in baseline weapon skills? Kinda sad if you ask me.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong I like my mercs and have waited since beta 2 for Mythic to &quot;fix&quot; us. Maybe one day that'll happen, but for now I think these are some issues that need to be addressed to Mythic.<br>
<br>
Carach<br>
50th Mercenary of <br>
The Eighth Direction<br>
Bedevere Server  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ucarach.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carach</A> at: 9/3/02 11:01:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/usalatp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SalatP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#000000>(9/4/02 5:22:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dw 50</span><hr size=1> Now that i have played my merc a bit, almost maxed out on BG1, tanked a bit and soloed a bit, i'm really liking it. Especially RvR. I am very seldom target #1 in a big brawl which means i can dish out pretty hefty damage. Casters go down in 2-4 hits depending on what they con. I love it when assassins try to kill me, i've yet to die to one 1 vs 1 other than that time i was in the middle of a tell and forgot to press enter. Needless to say i stood there for 10 seconds being beat upon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Defensive wise i seem to be doing good, having more Evade would rock tho, thats for sure. Offensive i'm pretty happy too. I do quite a lot of damage and by using positional styles i can deal a lot. I wouldn't mind dealing more damage tho, but i can see it being overpowering just to add more dmg with our current weaponry. Thats why i'm still thinking another line of damage or dirty tricks would be the way to go. Berzerkers should do more damage than us in pure melee considering what they are, but we should make up for it by kicking them where it hurts, etc.<br>
<br>
Oh, and dirty tricks is mad fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Saved my life several times. I even soloed 2 even con assassins by using it on 1, he fumbled the whole fight, and killing the other first. That was pretty funny <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In todays post on the Herald i saw that melee loving is under way. Let's hope something drips on us too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
